column2: • In Hebrew slang, the word sababa means ""all right,"" ""good,"" ""no problem.""
• ""Everything is cool"" has always been the attitude of Sababa Mediterranean Grill in Las Vegas, Nevada.

• The restaurant got its monikor when the original owner called his brother to ask some advice on their new restaurant. The customary response to the ""How are you"" inquiry is to answer with, ""Sababa,"" and when the brothers exchanged salutations, the proverbial light bulb went off, and their new restaurant had a name! When current owner, Effie Shencher bought SMG in 2005, he liked the story and agreed with the philosophy, so he kept the name, Sababa.

• Effie’s first culinary journey began in his mother’s kitchen as a young boy. It was there that his love for cooking grew. He pursued his passion and graduated from Tadmor Culinary School in Israel. Effie has been in the industry for 27 years, operating and owning restaurants and catering businesses in Las Vegas and Israel.
• Sababa looks forward to serving you with ""Everything is cool"" and “all is good” dining experience.
• For more information click here.

column2: • If you're keeping kosher in South Florida, you don't have to settle for a falafel joint the next time you're looking for a place to eat.

• L'Chaim Asian Cuisine & Steakhouse is certified by the Orthodox Rabbinic Board with chefs who hand-pick the freshest local meats and vegetables and use a selection of imported spices, seasonings, and authentic ingredients to ensure a great kosher dining experience.
• The menu is dine-in or takeaway and offers a wide spectrum of cuisine from sushi to steak designed to satisfy a variety of dietary concerns and dining preferences.

column2: • Kosher Without Borders is designed to help you find Kosher food made to Orthodox standards anywhere on Earth.
• We also list non-Orthodox providers and closed establishments to clear up any doubts you might have, if you come across them while searching online.
• Ethel's produces gluten-free cookies available for takeaway and gift wrapping. Great decoration.

column1: “All ingredients used in food production at establishments under Kosher Michigan’s certification must be approved by Rabbi Jason Miller and bear an approved kosher symbol (hechsher). No new ingredients or products may be introduced with prior approval from Rabbi Jason Miller. In most cases, only cheeses with a reliable kosher symbol are used in the production of food. If cheeses that do not bear a reliable kosher symbol are used, they must be USDA-approved cheeses made in the U.S.and the kosher certification letter must stipulate this. These cheeses are approved as kosher by the Conservative Movement through a legal ruling by the International Rabbinical Assembly’s Committee on Jewish Law and Standards (Yoreh Deah 87:10; Rabbi Kassel Abelson 1994).”",checked,,"Bakery,Food",,North America,USA,Michigan,,https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583868161943-29a9ec42256e?ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1171&q=80,(313) 469-1510,Kosher Michigan,https://ethelsbaking.com/,moderate,42.4602545,-82.9099604,"22314 Harper Ave. St. Clair Shores, MI 48080",,http://koshermichigan.com/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,14/8/2018,20/1/2021,,,,https://scontent-lga3-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/255521643_4931265603584226_1188117150914424788_n.jpg?_nc_cat=100&ccb=1-5&_nc_sid=8bfeb9&_nc_ohc=fBPzU26oHfoAX9Byge9&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.xx&oh=561996f33d0e543b56c99428f09edf05&oe=61A1AFC7 https://scontent-lga3-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t31.18172-8/26232435_1790468724330612_1628749545742724263_o.jpg?_nc_cat=108&ccb=1-5&_nc_sid=e3f864&_nc_ohc=J00r4CfCBMMAX8QKHRX&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.xx&oh=811b7377c014ca8814bc1cab78c371d2&oe=61C3856A https://scontent-lga3-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.18169-9/21230955_1645622005481952_6078638108465215423_n.jpg?_nc_cat=103&ccb=1-5&_nc_sid=e3f864&_nc_ohc=-7lnYjEAefYAX9i-abt&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.xx&oh=6a5ceb25f213982ba2bdd1b759299c04&oe=61C23966,,,,,,

column2: • Run by a fifth generation baker, 3 Brothers Bakery is the oldest Kosher bakery in Houston, serving both pareve and dairy.

• Including custom designed wedding, bar mitzvah and special occasion cakes. Eastern European and New York style pastries, dessert cakes, danish, coffee cakes and Eastern European breads (rye, pumpernickel, challah, bagels) provided daily.
• Ceremonial challahs (3, 6, and 10 pound plus custom shapes) available by special order. Commercial accounts welcome, as well.
• The Braeswood location is the only certified Kosher branch of 3 Brothers.
• This  restaurant is no longer kosher.

column2: • Seasons is a Kosher supermarket that invites you to shop for a wide variety of gourmet Kosher foods available at their stores. Including online shopping and delivery
• They offer Kosher grocery and gourmet food, fresh meat and fish, deli, bakery, fresh fruits and vegetables, dairy, yoghurt, cheese, ice cream, and more.

column2: • Shosh and Chookie’s Fresh-Mex is Houston’s first Kosher dairy food truck, offering a variety of breakfast tacos on homemade tortillas and other Tex-Mex favourites.
• They are open for breakfast and lunch on weekdays at locations in the heart of Houston’s Jewish community, and they are available for special events at your location.
• Hours and location are set weekly. Call, text, or follow them on Facebook to check their schedule or to book the truck.

column2: • Café Emunah is the only kosher restaurant in Fort Lauderdale and is mere steps from the Beach! It prides itself on offering an experience for your senses and an oasis for your mind, body and soul - a physical journey into your spiritual self.
• Upon entering, you feel enveloped by the warm and serene environment. The decor is upscale but sparse and features glass tables and blue fabric on the couches.

• Materials used in the restaurant are consistent with the eco-conscious elements of mysticism: napkins from recycled paper and pale blonde wood chairs that are ergonomic and simple in design, yet comfortable.
• The restaurant is also a tea bar and lounge with comfortable couches and a small library of books about Jewish mysticism.
• Its geographically central location makes it an ideal meeting spot for people in Miami to meet up with friends from Boca and the surrounding areas in between, such as Hollywood and Delray.

• It also makes for a convenient meal on the way to and from the airport, as it is only a 15-minute drive from the Ft. Lauderdale Airport. Café Emunah is the perfect ending to a day on the beach or a yummy preface to a romantic evening stroll.
• For more information click here.

column2: • offering delicious, homemade baked goods straight from our family to yours

• our kosher bakery offers homemade baked goods straight from our family to yours. Whether you’re stopping by for breakfast before work in the morning or picking up a few treats to bring home at night, Kaff’s Bake Shop has something for everyone to enjoy!

<li>At Kaff’s Bake Shop, we use only the finest ingredients as we prepare our pastries, Danishes and cakes fresh each morning. Additionally, we also offer a variety of salads, sandwiches and coffee for breakfast, lunch and take-out throughout the day. Our specials include rotating daily breakfast, weekly cakes and featured Shabbat items.

column1: We invite neighborhood residents and visitors alike to stop by and taste the delicious baked goods we have to offer! Please give us a call with any questions or special orders, then stop by one of our three area locations today to experience Kaff’s Bake Shop for yourself!

4739,Mountain Top Steakhouse at Chalet Hotel,"

    Open during summer only

column2: • Executive Chef Chaim Levi has created an excellent menu with trendy dishes Sous Vide meats, chicken and waffles, and specials that change daily.
• Call in advance for reservations at (845) 434-5124. They are open for dinner Sunday through Thursday, 5PM-11PM. Mountain Top is under the supervision of Rabbi Shmiel Berger (Mishkoltz Rav).

3755,Zayde's Kosher Kitchen,"

Central Florida's first full-Kosher premier catering service featuring international and American Kosher cuisine.

column2: • Located at one of Orlando’s award-winning meeting, convention, and vacation properties, Rosen Plaza Hotel, Zayde’s Kosher Catering is dedicated to delivering the highest quality Kosher catering.

• Offering on-site catering at all seven Rosen Hotels & Resorts, as well as off-site catering options; their talented culinary team led by Rosen Plaza’s Executive Chef Michael McMullen and Rosen Shingle Creek’s Executive Chef Jorge Oliveira, are committed to providing high-end, internationally-inspired Kosher cuisine, all within strict kashrut guidelines.
• Zayde’s state-of-the art Kosher culinary centre includes separate kitchens for Glatt Kosher meat, dairy, and pareve, all supervised by a full time on-site mashgiach.

12172,Peteet’s Cheesecake,"

Certification is questionable. Open on Shabbat.

column2: • Kosher Without Borders is designed to help you find Kosher food made to Orthodox standards anywhere on Earth.
• We also list non-Orthodox providers and closed establishments to clear up any doubts you might have, if you come across them while searching online.
• At Peteet’s Cheesecake every one of their gourmet Kosher cheesecakes is made entirely from scratch, with fresh and natural ingredients.

column1: All ingredients used in food production at establishments under Kosher Michigan’s certification must be approved by Rabbi Jason Miller and bear an approved kosher symbol (hechsher). No new ingredients or products may be introduced with prior approval from Rabbi Jason Miller. In most cases, only cheeses with a reliable kosher symbol are used in the production of food. If cheeses that do not bear a reliable kosher symbol are used, they must be USDA-approved cheeses made in the U.S.and the kosher certification letter must stipulate this. These cheeses are approved as kosher by the Conservative Movement through a legal ruling by the International Rabbinical Assembly’s Committee on Jewish Law and Standards (Yoreh Deah 87:10; Rabbi Kassel Abelson 1994).""",checked,,"Bakery,Food",,North America,USA,Michigan,,https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583868161943-29a9ec42256e?ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1171&q=80,+1 248-545-2253,Kosher Michigan,http://peteetscheesecakes.com/,moderate,42.4593635,-83.1851847,"13835 W Nine Mile Rd, Oak Park, MI 48237, USA",https://www.facebook.com/peteetsfamouscheesecakes,http://koshermichigan.com/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,13/8/2018,20/1/2021,,,,https://scontent-lga3-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.6435-9/156758386_3802596033158300_128975154991400574_n.jpg?_nc_cat=102&ccb=1-5&_nc_sid=8bfeb9&_nc_ohc=p1jRdp5YmiwAX9HNNVy&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.xx&oh=12485e9ad223cb28193a405cb2f4f0fd&oe=61C18357 https://scontent-lga3-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.6435-9/163654964_3843279829089920_5610165481049605858_n.jpg?_nc_cat=105&ccb=1-5&_nc_sid=a26aad&_nc_ohc=NazYPxO-7GMAX_FMnaD&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.xx&oh=12ad425663c9680a979886f7f515f0bc&oe=61C384A2 https://scontent-lga3-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.6435-9/185348148_3999769160107652_8617782563867627126_n.jpg?_nc_cat=110&ccb=1-5&_nc_sid=a26aad&_nc_ohc=K4PeY9g2rbUAX9GSLWT&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.xx&oh=4e81a563b4f0b70c72e0e396c88862ce&oe=61C15D1B,,,,,,

9168,Chabad of Central Florida,"

Friendly Chabad in Tampa Florida.

column2: • Conveniently located, 3-minute walk to the Hyde Park Hotel, amazing synagogue, perfect for Shabbos in Tampa.
• Shabbat/Yom Tov Guest Rooms: There are rooms upstairs of the Shul available under reservation for Shabbat and holidays.
• 1. Hyde Park Hotel - (813) 254 2000 2105 W Bristol Avenue, Tampa, Florida This hotel is just one block away from Bais David!
• 2. Epicurean Hotel - (813) 999 8700 -1207 S Howard Ave (5-star hotel).
• 3. University Inn - (813) 253 0851 x0 830 W Kennedy Blvd.

• Chabad provides strictly kosher meals directly to your accommodation. They also provide packed lunches for day trips and picnics. All meals are prepared under the supervision of the Orthodox Kashrut Committee of Tampa.  If you have any queries then please don't hesitate to email to info@chabadofcentralflorida.com.

• The weekly Kiddush luncheon is sponsored by families in the community in a rotating fashion and because of their generosity, everyone that attends Chabad enjoys a delicious lunch. They would like to open the opportunity for sponsorship to you.

3424,Great American Health Bar,"

Healthful food like omelets, wraps & baked potatoes served in a diner-style setting.

column2: • If you're searching for a quick and wholesome meal in Midtown, look no further than The Great American Health Bar.

• It's near Central Park (perfect for a take-out lunch)and just below Cafe Classico. Whether you're in the area catching a live taping of The Late Show with Stephen Colbert, or attending a concert at Carnegie Hall, you don't have too far to schlep to get here.
• The location makes it easy to get to from Columbus Circle, and the Plaza Hotel. And it's just a few blocks from Broadway.

• This place it's been around for over 25 years, it's also one of the only dairy waiter service Kosher restaurants in Midtown. Don't be surprised if you find yourself rubbing shoulders with a big shot.

• Celebrities and models often visit Great American for their meals. During the day, the restaurant gets many individuals from the business world for lunch, and many nearby office buildings order their meals from the Great American Health Bar.

13054,Kish Kash,"

No Kosher certification. Opens on Shabbat.

column2: • They do not have a Kosher certification and they open on Shabbat.
• Kish-Kash, the newest concept by New York City’s leading Israeli/Middle Eastern Chef and restaurateur, Einat Admony, opened at 455 Hudson Street on June 18, 2018.

• Named for the sieve traditionally used to make couscous, Kish-Kash is the first-ever couscous bar in New York City specialising in hand-rolled, hand-sieved Moroccan couscous and authentic North African Jewish cuisine.
• Kish-Kash is a casual dining concept with a specialised menu featuring real Moroccan couscous, braised meats, fish, salads, challah, pickled veggies, and wines from Israel and North Africa.

• They offer chocolates ""made fresh on premises,"" using a three-generation European style family recipe.

• The ""made fresh on premises"" concept means that chocolate items do not come pre-packaged from headquarters, rather than items are prepared and dipped at each individual retail location allowing their franchise owners the flexibility to be creative and customise their fresh products to the customer's request.
• Their products are sold in a very cosy and friendly environment.

4235,Levy's Of Hollywood,"

This family-owned, kosher eatery serves up traditional shawarma & kebabs in a low-key atmosphere.

column2: • For over 20 years, Levys kosher of hollywood has been synonymous with Middle Eastern fine dining.
• Liz Levy executive chef/owner takes the cuisine and culture of her homeland to the next level with a breathtaking restaurant and delicious cuisine.
• The Chef's mastery of traditional spices and flavors makes each dish an opportunity to experience classics and delicacies in new and exciting ways.
• Every plate becomes a culinary journey. Levys kosher of Hollywood also features homemade desserts to sophisticated tastes.
• For more information click here.
